Name: stringutil
Synopsis: Utilities for converting and manipulating data to and from strings

Variables.Name: ExpandEnvPreserveIfEmpty
Variables.Comment:
If set to true, ExpandEnv() will preserve ${...} sequences whose resulting value would yield an empty string.
Fallback and formatting values are still supported, as the determination of value emptiness is made after parsing
the sequence.  This is to avoid unset environment variables resulting in the escape sequences being erased, which is often
the case when running ExpandEnv() against various shell languages (Bash, et. al)

Functions.Name: Elide
Functions.Comment: Truncate the given string to a certain number of characters.
Functions.Signature: Elide(in string, charcount int, trailer ...string) string

Functions.Name: ElideRight
Functions.Comment: Truncate the given string to a certain number of characters from the end.
Functions.Signature: ElideRight(in string, charcount int, leader ...string) string

Functions.Name: ElideWords
Functions.Comment: Truncate the given string to a certain number of words.

Functions.Name: ExpandEnv
Functions.Comment:
Return the given string with environment variable substitution sequences
expanded and (optionally) formatted.  This function operates similarly to
os.ExpandEnv, but accepts custom fmt.Printf formatting directives.

Functions.Name: HasAnyPrefix
Functions.Comment: HasPrefix tests whether the string s begins with any prefix in prefixes.

Functions.Name: HasAnySuffix
Functions.Comment: HasSuffix tests whether the string s begins with any suffix in suffixes.

Functions.Name: IsHexadecimal
Functions.Comment:
Returns whether the given string is a hexadecimal number. If the string is
prefixed with "0x", the prefix is removed first. If length is greater than 0,
the length of the input (excluding prefix) is checked as well.

Functions.Name: IsMixedCase
Functions.Comment:
Returns whether the letters (Unicode Catgeory 'L') in a given string are
homogenous in case (all upper-case or all lower-case).

Functions.Name: IsSurroundedBy
Functions.Signature: IsSurroundedBy(inI interface{}, prefix string, suffix string) bool

Functions.Name: PrefixEach
Functions.Comment: Prefix each element in the given string slice with prefix.

Functions.Name: PrefixIf
Functions.Comment: Prefix the given string if it is non-empty

Functions.Name: PrefixLines
Functions.Comment: Takes the given string, splits it into lines, and prefixes each line with the given prefix string.

Functions.Name: SplitLines
Functions.Comment: Split the given input into lines.

Functions.Name: SplitPair
Functions.Comment:
Split the given string into two parts.  If there is only one resulting part,
that part will be the first return value and the second return value will be empty.

Functions.Name: SplitPairRight
Functions.Comment:
Split the given string into two parts from the right. If there is only one resulting part,
that part will be the first return value and the second return value will be empty.

Functions.Name: SplitPairRightTrailing
Functions.Comment:
Split the given string into two parts.  If there is only one resulting part,
that part will be the second return value and the first return value will be empty.

Functions.Name: SplitPairTrailing
Functions.Comment:
Split the given string into two parts.  If there is only one resulting part,
that part will be the second return value and the first return value will be empty.

Functions.Name: SplitPairTrimSpace
Functions.Comment: Identical to SplitPair, but trims any leading and trailing whitespace from each output value.

Functions.Name: SplitTriple
Functions.Signature: SplitTriple(in string, delimiter string) (string, string, string)

Functions.Name: SplitTripleTrimSpace
Functions.Comment: Identical to SplitPair, but trims any leading and trailing whitespace from each output value.
Functions.Signature: SplitTripleTrimSpace(in string, delimiter string) (string, string, string)

Functions.Name: SplitWords
Functions.Comment: Split the given string into words.

Functions.Name: Squeeze
Functions.Comment:
Return the given string with sequences repeating character replaced with a
single instance of that character.

Functions.Name: SqueezeFunc
Functions.Comment:
Return the given string with sequences of characters matching the given function
replaced with a single instance of that character.

Functions.Name: SqueezeSpace
Functions.Comment:
Return the given string with sequences of whitespace characters replaced with
a single instance of that character.

Functions.Name: SuffixEach
Functions.Comment: Suffix each element in the given string slice with suffix.

Functions.Name: SuffixIf
Functions.Comment: Suffix the given string if it is non-empty

Functions.Name: SuffixLines
Functions.Comment: Takes the given string, splits it into lines, and suffixes each line with the given suffix string.

Functions.Name: Thousandify
Functions.Signature: Thousandify(in interface{}, separator string, decimal string) string

Functions.Name: Unwrap
Functions.Comment: Return the given string with the given prefix and suffix removed.
Functions.Signature: Unwrap(in string, prefix string, suffix string) string

Functions.Name: Wrap
Functions.Comment: Return the given string with prefixed and suffixed with other strings.
Functions.Signature: Wrap(in string, prefix string, suffix string) string

Functions.Name: WrapEach
Functions.Comment: Wrap each element in the given string slice with prefix and suffix.

Functions.Name: WrapIf
Functions.Comment: Wrap the given string if it is non-empty
Functions.Signature: WrapIf(in string, prefix string, suffix string) string

ScanInterceptor.Name: ScanInterceptor

Methods.Name: BytesScanned
Methods.Comment: Return the total number of bytes this scanner has scanned.

Methods.Name: Intercept
Methods.Comment:
Add an intercept sequence and handler.  If the sequence is already registered, its handler
function will be replaced with this one.

Methods.Name: InterceptCounts
Methods.Comment: Returns a map of intercept sequences and the number of times each one was fired.

Methods.Name: Scan
Methods.Comment: Implements the bufio.SplitFunc function signature for use in a bufio.Scanner.
Methods.Signature: Scan(data []byte, atEOF bool) (advance int, token []byte, err error)

ScanInterceptor.Comment:
A ScanInterceptor is used as a SplitFunc on a bufio.Scanner.  It will look at the stream of bytes being scanned for
specific substrings.  The registered handler function associated with a substring will be called whenever it is seen
in the stream.  The passthrough SplitFunc is called as normal.  This allows for a stream to be
split and processed while also being inspected for specific content, allowing the user to react to that content
as it comes by.
